Kaimini
=======

Introduction:

Documentation:
  The API documentation can be found here:
    http://www.physik.uni-wuerzburg.de/~fthomas/kaimini/doc/

Dependencies:
  Kaimini is written in C++. To build it, the C++ Standard Library, some
  parts of the Boost C++ Libraries[1], Minuit2[2], the GNU Scientific
  Library (GSL)[3], and CMake[4] are required.

  [1] http://www.boost.org/
  [2] http://www.cern.ch/minuit
  [3] http://www.gnu.org/software/gsl/
  [4] http://www.cmake.org/

  For development of Kaimini additional software is required. Doxygen[5]
  is used for building the API documentation and CppUnit[6] is required
  to compile the unit tests.

  [5] http://www.doxygen.org/
  [6] http://cppunit.sourceforge.net/

Installation:
  To compile Kaimini and to install the 'kaimini' executable into
  /usr/local/bin run these commands in Kaimini's source tree:
    mkdir build
    cd build
    cmake ..
    make
    sudo make install

Source code:
  For Kaimini's development the Git version control system is used. The
  Git repository can be inspected and browsed online at GitHub:
    http://github.com/fthomas/kaimini

  To clone the repository use this command:
    git clone git://github.com/fthomas/kaimini.git

Issues and feedback:
  For bug reports, feature requests, or general feedback either use the
  issue tracker[7] or write me an email[8].

  [7] http://github.com/fthomas/kaimini/issues
  [8] fthomas@physik.uni-wuerzburg.de

